Java

*   We use Java as our programming language and Selenium WebDriver for browser automation.
====================================================================================================
Maven

*   A build tool that manages project dependencies (like Selenium, TestNG).
*   It helps keep libraries up to date and makes the project easier to share.
====================================================================================================
 TestNG

*   A testing framework for structuring tests, running them in parallel, and generating HTML reports.
*   Helps us organize test cases into suites and groups.
====================================================================================================
Page Object Model (POM)

*   Design pattern to organize your Selenium code.
*   Each web page has a separate Java class (Page Object) containing locators and actions.
====================================================================================================
Feature Files (Cucumber)

*   In BDD (Behavior Driven Development), feature files use Gherkin language to write test scenarios.
====================================================================================================
Step Definitions

*   Java methods that link the steps in the feature files to Selenium code.
====================================================================================================
Properties File

*   A .properties file stores configurations like URLs, browser type, username, etc.
*   Easy to change settings without touching the code.
====================================================================================================